headline: Dow Jones' revolving door: What happened to 5 companies after that were dropped from the DJIA
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA) is the oldest stock index in America. Founded in 1896 by Charles Dow, Edward Jones, and Charles Bergstresser, it’s considered a benchmark for the performance of the country’s large, blue-chip companies—those big household names, like Home Depot (HD), Johnson ...
